<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-92CE7882-1B62-426A-AC5B-96AA3C0926BD" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-92CE7882-1B62-426A-AC5B-96AA3C0926BD" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">05 How to adjust the tension of the printhead carriage drive belt </title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-173AF84C-D126-4DD5-8ABA-ADD08113B9D4"><p class="- topic/p ">This adjustment is the mechanical belt tension of the printhead carriage drive belt. 
</p><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-759936E5-8F2F-400C-8A41-CDD4FA494426"><p class="- topic/p ">This adjustment can only be done after the mechanical release of the drive belt tension of the carriage belt. Example: after replacement of the drive belt or refitting the drive belt. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The adjustment must be done before the start-up (Initialization) of the printer. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">After the initialization of the printer the position of the bolt has no reference anymore. 
</p></note></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Adjustment</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-982BAB96-F1AC-436A-A6A8-B6CC211033FE" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ul id="UL_FC1647DBE66F40EAAF0086BB3E0A9CE1" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_E562AA275D63474CB2E1FE6DD165A477" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Printhead carriage drive belt is not installed. 
</p></li></ul></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_A392D23B9FA5434A8095E72A33F001E1" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_BFC835835B5440A98A2DF72417BDB02D" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Screwdriver. 
</p></li><li id="LI_290738A2E21242D1A21ED2B5C14AE640" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Small screwdriver. 
</p></li><li id="LI_929C0F12811B4096BB70DA320BD9C6C8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Protective gloves: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Microflex</b> 93-260 gloves. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-DB340B14-87E5-4FDB-8108-245D16C84FF1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-1C6A5506-8461-4BFD-8B7C-FB47C7EF289A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-72BC1DEC-D4D6-4701-BA70-C6803D6775DA-low.png" id="IMAGE_CB67C5D682784AFE93225DD297C4918D" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-72BC1DEC-D4D6-4701-BA70-C6803D6775DA-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to adjust</title><table id="GUID-BDB87D50-9E70-4086-AC9E-FA7970C76B0D" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the pin / screwdriver (used to lock the position of the bracket). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Turn the bolt -A- counter clock-wise till the edge of the bolt is set to 0 +/- 0.5 mm. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_DCF7966505634F1D8C8011AB0E9C5B61" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-57B805E0-8806-4F6A-86DD-2E11417B04F1-low.png" id="IMAGE_17828080898D4EA7BA80CD03A1693AA9" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-57B805E0-8806-4F6A-86DD-2E11417B04F1-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_AEEB5781278B45C0AADAABC2ECF1BE07" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-1A72E5F5-1CA1-4182-9C82-8484ECDD593A-low.png" id="IMAGE_CE26E08C48964DE2BB14D893F3481B89" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-1A72E5F5-1CA1-4182-9C82-8484ECDD593A-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-539C2D6A-19DE-44EE-8367-DF76C5C622A4" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-8EAEA36C-CA08-4B0B-BE32-AD6DC5F14773-low.jpg" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8EAEA36C-CA08-4B0B-BE32-AD6DC5F14773-low.jpg"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><note id="GUID-05882E3E-259C-4EB0-816E-2A11B398F6EA" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Check that the ruler guide is in the correct position and holds the ruler in place.
